p247
aVThose visits are expensive, and in order to maintain her model,
p248
aVshe's got to see a lot of clients to cover costs.
p249
aVBut Jennie doesn't have to spend a ton of time with each woman,
p250
aVif all of the members of her team can provide the support, information
p251
aVand care that her clients need.
p252
aVThe beauty of Jennie's model is that she actually believes
p253
aVit can be implemented in pretty much any health care setting.
p254
aVIt's a revolution in care just waiting to happen.
p255
aa(lp256
VThese problems I've been sharing with you are big.
p257
aVThey come from long histories of racism, classism,
p258
aVa society based on race and class stratification.
p259
aVThey involve elaborate physiological mechanisms
p260
aVmeant to protect us,
p261
aVthat, when overstimulated, actually make us sick.
p262
aVBut if there's one thing I've learned from my work as a doula,
p263
aVit's that a little bit of unconditional support can go a really long way.
p264
aVHistory has shown that people are incredibly resilient,
p265
